Ryan Ficklin (individual)

Running the program should be performed similar to the video provided in the lab
specification. Multiple terminal windows or other multiplexing will be required.

Then run:
$go run server.go
$go run client.go 1
$go run client.go 2
$go run client.go 3
$go run client.go 4
$go run client.go 5
$go run client.go 6
$go run client.go 7
$go run client.go 8

I had a bash script that opened up these terminal windows for me and ran the
commands for testing. I have included this script, however, it is designed
specifically for my shell (Konsole from KDE Plasma), so I do not expect it to
be very portable and thus make no guarantees about its performance. However,
I figured I should still include it because it is used during the video demo
attached.

See my lab report (lab2report.pdf) for any other details about the program
